============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Virtue Ethics
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Ethics is about developing virtuous character traits
Philosopher:  Aristotle
Example:      A courageous person acts courageously habitually; ethics is becoming good

